An overview of all Disney-related events that occurred in the year 2005.

Theatrical releases[]

February 11 - Pooh's Heffalump Movie is released to generally positive reviews from critics, but only a modest success at the box office.

Theme park and resorts happenings[]

January 20 - Disney's River Country is confirmed to be closed permanently at Walt Disney World Resort.

February 13 - An incident occurs at the Magic Kingdom park in Florida, in which a 77-year-old woman dies while riding Pirates of the Caribbean in Adventureland.

February 26 - Cinderella's Surprise Celebration has its final performances at the Magic Kingdom.

March 17 - The Florida version of Cinderellabration premieres at the Magic Kingdom.

April 1 - Disney's Blizzard Beach celebrates its 10th anniversary.

April 9 - Space Mountain: Mission 2 opens in Discoveryland at Disneyland Paris.

May 5 - Disneyland begins its 50th Anniversary celebration.

Buzz Lightyear Astro Blasters opens in Tomorrowland.

Remember... Dreams Come True, Walt Disney's Parade of Dreams, and The Happiest Faces on Earth officially debut there.

Block Party Bash officially debuts at Disney's California Adventure.

Cinderellabration officially debuts at the Magic Kingdom.

Soarin' opens in The Land Pavilion at Epcot.

Lights, Motors, Action! Extreme Stunt Show opens in Streets of America at Disney-MGM Studios.

Wishes officially debuts at Disneyland Paris.

June 29 - 25 guests are injured on California Screamin' in Paradise Pier at Disney's California Adventure.

July 15 - Space Mountain reopens in Tomorrowland at Disneyland after a two-year rehab, which is part of Happiest Homecoming on Earth celebration.

July 17 - Disneyland and Disneyland Resort celebrates its 50th anniversary.

July 21 - Raging Spirits opens in Lost River Delta at Tokyo DisneySea.

August 16 - Inspiration Lake Recreation Centre opens at the Hong Kong Disneyland Resort.

August 21 - The Living Seas closes in Future World at Epcot to make way for The Seas with Nemo & Friends.

September 12

Hong Kong Disneyland on Lantau Island, Hong Kong opens to the public, becoming the fifth Disney Resort destination to do so and the third international one to do so.

Super Duper Jumpin' Time premiered at Tokyo Disneyland.

December 9 - Journey into Narnia: Creating the Lion, the Witch, and the Wardrobe opens at Disney-MGM Studios.
